service: Transit Gateway Network Manager (Network Manager) enables you to create a global network, in which you can monitor your Amazon Web Services and on-premises networks that are built around transit gateways.

operations.AcceptAttachment:
Accepts a core network attachment request.

Once the attachment request is accepted by a core network owner, the attachment is created and connected to a core network.
operations.AssociateConnectPeer:
Associates a core network Connect peer with a device and optionally, with a link.

If you specify a link, it must be associated with the specified device. You can only associate core network Connect peers that have been created on a core network Connect attachment on a core network.
operations.AssociateCustomerGateway:
Associates a customer gateway with a device and optionally, with a link. If you specify a link, it must be associated with the specified device.

You can only associate customer gateways that are connected to a VPN attachment on a transit gateway. The transit gateway must be registered in your global network. When you register a transit gateway, customer gateways that are connected to the transit gateway are automatically included in the global network. To list customer gateways that are connected to a transit gateway, use the DescribeVpnConnections EC2 API and filter by transit-gateway-id.

You cannot associate a customer gateway with more than one device and link.
operations.AssociateLink: Associates a link to a device. A device can be associated to multiple links and a link can be associated to multiple devices. The device and link must be in the same global network and the same site.
operations.AssociateTransitGatewayConnectPeer:
Associates a transit gateway Connect peer with a device, and optionally, with a link. If you specify a link, it must be associated with the specified device.

You can only associate transit gateway Connect peers that have been created on a transit gateway that's registered in your global network.

You cannot associate a transit gateway Connect peer with more than one device and link.
operations.CreateConnectAttachment:
Creates a core network Connect attachment from a specified core network attachment.

A core network Connect attachment is a GRE-based tunnel attachment that you can use to establish a connection between a core network and an appliance. A core network Connect attachment uses an existing VPC attachment as the underlying transport mechanism.
operations.CreateConnectPeer: Creates a core network connect peer for a specified core network connect attachment between a core network and an appliance. The peer address and transit gateway address must be the same IP address family (IPv4 or IPv6).
operations.CreateConnection: Creates a connection between two devices. The devices can be a physical or virtual appliance that connects to a third-party appliance in a VPC, or a physical appliance that connects to another physical appliance in an on-premises network.
operations.CreateCoreNetwork: Creates a core network as part of your global network, and optionally, with a core network policy.
operations.CreateDevice: Creates a new device in a global network. If you specify both a site ID and a location, the location of the site is used for visualization in the Network Manager console.
operations.CreateLink: Creates a new link for a specified site.
operations.CreateSite: Creates a new site in a global network.
operations.CreateSiteToSiteVpnAttachment: Creates a site-to-site VPN attachment on an edge location of a core network.
operations.CreateVpcAttachment: Creates a VPC attachment on an edge location of a core network.
operations.DeleteAttachment: Deletes an attachment. Supports all attachment types.
operations.DeleteConnection: Deletes the specified connection in your global network.
operations.DeleteCoreNetwork: Deletes a core network along with all core network policies. This can only be done if there are no attachments on a core network.
operations.DeleteCoreNetworkPolicyVersion: Deletes a policy version from a core network. You can't delete the current LIVE policy.
operations.DeleteDevice: Deletes an existing device. You must first disassociate the device from any links and customer gateways.
operations.DeleteGlobalNetwork: Deletes an existing global network. You must first delete all global network objects (devices, links, and sites) and deregister all transit gateways.
operations.DeleteLink: Deletes an existing link. You must first disassociate the link from any devices and customer gateways.
operations.DeleteResourcePolicy: Deletes a resource policy for the specified resource. This revokes the access of the principals specified in the resource policy.
operations.DeleteSite: Deletes an existing site. The site cannot be associated with any device or link.
operations.DeregisterTransitGateway: Deregisters a transit gateway from your global network. This action does not delete your transit gateway, or modify any of its attachments. This action removes any customer gateway associations.
operations.DescribeGlobalNetworks: Describes one or more global networks. By default, all global networks are described. To describe the objects in your global network, you must use the appropriate Get* action. For example, to list the transit gateways in your global network, use GetTransitGatewayRegistrations.
operations.DisassociateConnectPeer: Disassociates a core network Connect peer from a device and a link.
operations.DisassociateCustomerGateway: Disassociates a customer gateway from a device and a link.
operations.DisassociateLink: Disassociates an existing device from a link. You must first disassociate any customer gateways that are associated with the link.
operations.DisassociateTransitGatewayConnectPeer: Disassociates a transit gateway Connect peer from a device and link.
operations.ExecuteCoreNetworkChangeSet: Executes a change set on your core network. Deploys changes globally based on the policy submitted..
operations.GetConnectAttachment: Returns information about a core network Connect attachment.
operations.GetConnectPeer: Returns information about a core network Connect peer.
operations.GetConnectPeerAssociations: Returns information about a core network Connect peer associations.
operations.GetConnections: Gets information about one or more of your connections in a global network.
operations.GetCoreNetwork: Returns information about a core network. By default it returns the LIVE policy.
operations.GetCoreNetworkChangeSet: Returns a change set between the LIVE core network policy and a submitted policy.
operations.GetCoreNetworkPolicy: Gets details about a core network policy. You can get details about your current live policy or any previous policy version.
operations.GetCustomerGatewayAssociations: Gets the association information for customer gateways that are associated with devices and links in your global network.
operations.GetDevices: Gets information about one or more of your devices in a global network.
operations.GetLinkAssociations: Gets the link associations for a device or a link. Either the device ID or the link ID must be specified.
operations.GetLinks:
Gets information about one or more links in a specified global network.

If you specify the site ID, you cannot specify the type or provider in the same request. You can specify the type and provider in the same request.
operations.GetNetworkResourceCounts: Gets the count of network resources, by resource type, for the specified global network.
operations.GetNetworkResourceRelationships: Gets the network resource relationships for the specified global network.
operations.GetNetworkResources:
Describes the network resources for the specified global network.

The results include information from the corresponding Describe call for the resource, minus any sensitive information such as pre-shared keys.
operations.GetNetworkRoutes: Gets the network routes of the specified global network.
operations.GetNetworkTelemetry: Gets the network telemetry of the specified global network.
operations.GetRouteAnalysis: Gets information about the specified route analysis.
operations.GetSiteToSiteVpnAttachment: Returns information about a site-to-site VPN attachment.
operations.GetSites: Gets information about one or more of your sites in a global network.
operations.GetTransitGatewayConnectPeerAssociations: Gets information about one or more of your transit gateway Connect peer associations in a global network.
operations.GetTransitGatewayRegistrations: Gets information about the transit gateway registrations in a specified global network.
operations.ListAttachments: Returns a list of core network attachments.
operations.ListConnectPeers: Returns a list of core network Connect peers.
operations.ListCoreNetworkPolicyVersions: Returns a list of core network policy versions.
operations.ListCoreNetworks: Returns a list of owned and shared core networks.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Lists the tags for a specified resource.
operations.PutCoreNetworkPolicy: Creates a new, immutable version of a core network policy. A subsequent change set is created showing the differences between the LIVE policy and the submitted policy.
operations.RegisterTransitGateway: Registers a transit gateway in your global network. The transit gateway can be in any Amazon Web Services Region, but it must be owned by the same Amazon Web Services account that owns the global network. You cannot register a transit gateway in more than one global network.
operations.RestoreCoreNetworkPolicyVersion: Restores a previous policy version as a new, immutable version of a core network policy. A subsequent change set is created showing the differences between the LIVE policy and restored policy.
operations.StartRouteAnalysis: Starts analyzing the routing path between the specified source and destination. For more information, see Route Analyzer.
operations.UpdateConnection: Updates the information for an existing connection. To remove information for any of the parameters, specify an empty string.
operations.UpdateCoreNetwork: Updates the description of a core network.
operations.UpdateDevice: Updates the details for an existing device. To remove information for any of the parameters, specify an empty string.
operations.UpdateGlobalNetwork: Updates an existing global network. To remove information for any of the parameters, specify an empty string.
operations.UpdateLink: Updates the details for an existing link. To remove information for any of the parameters, specify an empty string.
operations.UpdateNetworkResourceMetadata: Updates the resource metadata for the specified global network.
operations.UpdateSite: Updates the information for an existing site. To remove information for any of the parameters, specify an empty string.

RouteAnalysisCompletion.base: Describes the status of an analysis at completion.

refs.RouteAnalysisCompletion$ReasonCode:
The reason code. Available only if a connection is not found.

  • BLACKHOLE_ROUTE_FOR_DESTINATION_FOUND - Found a black hole route with the destination CIDR block.

  • CYCLIC_PATH_DETECTED - Found the same resource multiple times while traversing the path.

  • INACTIVE_ROUTE_FOR_DESTINATION_FOUND - Found an inactive route with the destination CIDR block.

  • MAX_HOPS_EXCEEDED - Analysis exceeded 64 hops without finding the destination.

  • ROUTE_NOT_FOUND - Cannot find a route table with the destination CIDR block.

  • TGW_ATTACH_ARN_NO_MATCH - Found an attachment, but not with the correct destination ARN.

  • TGW_ATTACH_NOT_FOUND - Cannot find an attachment.

  • TGW_ATTACH_NOT_IN_TGW - Found an attachment, but not to the correct transit gateway.

  • TGW_ATTACH_STABLE_ROUTE_TABLE_NOT_FOUND - The state of the route table association is not associated.

refs.RouteAnalysisCompletion$ResultCode: The result of the analysis. If the status is NOT_CONNECTED, check the reason code.
